index 6db9530d..b9223b2e 100644
--- a/docs/cli-reference.md
+++ b/docs/cli-reference.md
@@ -254,6 +254,25 @@ takt #6 --workflow dual
 
 **Requirements:** [GitHub CLI](https://cli.github.com/) (`gh`) must be installed and authenticated.
 
+## GitHub PR Review Tasks
+
+You can use a pull request as task input. TAKT fetches the PR body, conversation comments, and review thread comments, then turns them into task context.
+
+```bash
+# Start interactive mode from PR review context
+takt --pr 123
+
+# Save PR review context as a pending task
+takt add --pr 123
+
+# Run a workflow directly from PR review context
+takt --pipeline --pr 123 --workflow default
+```
+
+When PR comments contain Markdown image syntax or HTML `<img src="...">` references to GitHub attachment URLs, TAKT downloads supported images and stores them as task attachments. Saved tasks place the files under `.takt/tasks/{slug}/attachments/` and list them in `order.md`, for example `attachments/image-1.png`. Pipeline `--pr` runs stage the same attachment-backed task spec before execution.
+
+PR image downloads are intentionally limited to GitHub attachment URLs. Supported image formats are PNG, JPEG, GIF, and WebP. TAKT validates both `Content-Type` and image magic bytes, rejects mismatches and unsupported data, enforces a 10 MiB image limit, and rejects redirects outside the allowed GitHub attachment hosts. Private repository images require an authenticated GitHub CLI; TAKT uses `gh auth token` for these requests.
+
 ## Task Management Commands
 
 Batch processing using `.takt/tasks.yaml` with task directories under `.takt/tasks/{slug}/`. Useful for accumulating multiple tasks and executing them together later.
